---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/base-layout.astro";
import { SITE_PERSONAL_URL, SITE_REPO_URL } from "@/lib/utils/site";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · Smol"
  description="Why I built Smol, and why I still reach for it every week."
>
  <section class="grid gap-8">
    <div class="max-w-[42rem] space-y-4">
      <p class="text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/40">
        Why I built this
      </p>
      <h1
        class="max-w-[20ch] font-display text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.2rem)] leading-[1.02] tracking-[-0.05em] text-text"
      >
        I wanted a simple, clean compressor I didn't have to pay for.
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[1rem] leading-7 text-white/58">
        Every other compressor wants something from you: a cap on how many
        images per session, a file that's too big for the free tier, ads, or the
        genuinely useful parts (download the best result, drop in a whole
        folder) locked behind a monthly plan. TinyPNG was handy until the limit.
        Squash was great until it stopped being maintained. I just wanted to
        shrink what I needed and get on with my day.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[1rem] leading-7 text-white/58">
        Smol runs in your browser and keeps everything on your machine. You drop
        images in, it finds the smaller version for you, and you can slide the
        before and after side by side, so you're never guessing which one to
        keep.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm text-white/68">
        <a
          class="underline decoration-white/15 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-white/55 hover:text-text"
          href={SITE_REPO_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          GitHub
        </a>
        <a
          class="underline decoration-white/15 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-white/55 hover:text-text"
          href={SITE_PERSONAL_URL}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          andersonjoseph.com
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid gap-4 border-t border-border pt-5">
    <p class="text-[0.72rem] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-white/40">
      What matters
    </p>
    <div
      class="grid gap-3 text-[0.98rem] leading-7 text-white/58 sm:grid-cols-2"
    >
      <p>
        Local-first. Batch compression. Side-by-side checks. Format conversion
        when you actually need it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Built with jSquash, imagequant for pngquant-style PNG compression, web
        workers, Astro, and a small React layer. The project is now GPL-3.0.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
